CatDescriptText: Mr. A. N. Schindehette, insurance agent, Greentree, was part of the Pittsburghers Speak Up column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 16, 1961, pg. 7 with question: "Do you think the so-called 'store-front' churches, and those who are known generally as 'self-styled preachers,' are an asset or a liability to the community." answer reads: "I definitely don't think they are assets. The churches should be held in esteem and therefore be more than 'store fronts'."
